node.text:
❓ What’s your favorite World Showcase pavilion?

🏢 There are 12 countries that were proposed for the World Showcase that were seriously considered, but unfortunately never built. Today we’ll dive into the first six - check back tomorrow to see the second half!

🇩🇰 DENMARK: In the mid-90s, this country came extremely close to being built. It would’ve featured a miniature Tivoli gardens (which is an amusement park in the center of Copenhagen)!

🇨🇷 COSTA RICA: This was shown in early plans for the Works Showcase and would’ve featured a "crystal palace" hosting tropical gardens, birds and waterfalls.

🇮🇷 IRAN: Proposed before Epcot was built, Iran would’ve featured a dark ride through Persian history. However, when the Shah was overthrown in 1979, the idea was scrapped.

🇸🇪 SCANDANAVIAN: At one point, Disney approached several Scandanavian nations together and suggested they all sign on to one combined pavilion, in order to make it more cost effective. However, only Norway signed up, hence why they have their own pavilion today. 

🇷🇺 RUSSIA: In the early 90s, plans were drawn up for a Russian pavilion featuring a recreation of St. Basil's Cathedral with a show about the country’s history, but was cancelled due to the collapse of the Soviet Union.

🇮🇱 ISRAEL: This was supposed to be one of the original World Showcase countries and was even shown in early park advertisements but due to budget cuts and time constraints, was never built.
.
.
.
.
.

❓ Have you ever seen a celebrity at Disney? Let us know in the comments! 

🏴‍☠️ Is it true that Johnny Depp will replace his animatronic on Pirates of the Caribbean to surprise guests? Surprisingly, this is true! It has happened at Disneyland. 

♟ However, this has only happened a select few times. People can make it seem like it happens frequently, but it’s super unlikely that it will ever happen again, sadly! 
.
.
.
.
.

❓ Do you prefer to stay off-site or on-site?

🏢 Today we’re doing a FULL REVIEW of the @courtyardlakebv! This Disney Springs Good Neighbor hotel was recently completely remodeled, so it’s BRAND NEW. It features:

🌴 Two pools (one has a slide and splash pad!) with cabanas and lounge chairs, perfect for cooling off after a long day in the parks

🍸 An indoor/outdoor bar with TVs, pool tables, corn hole, and tons of lounge areas

🏋️‍♂️ A 24-hour fitness center, newly updated

🚃 Complimentary shuttles to Disney, Universal Studios, and Sea World

☕️ A full ACTUAL Starbucks (not just a “Proudly Serving Starbucks Coffee”), a 24/7 marketplace, and a breakfast restaurant

🏘 Suites and connecting rooms are available, so there’s plenty of options for bigger families

🧺 Coin-operated laundry onsite

#hosted #courtyardlakebv
.
.
.
.
.

node.text:
❓Will you pay for Genie+? Let us know in the comments!
 
Let’s look a little deeper into this new system!

🧞‍♂️Genie+ is a paid service that gives access to 3 things. 

📸 Disney Photopass - unlimited downloads of Photopass photos and ride photos, and some fun Photopass lenses 

🎵 Behind the Scenes Audio Tales - recorded in depth facts about the parks (I’ve heard rumors John Stamos is narrating!)

⚡️ Lightning Lane - the new name for Fastpass. This allows for expedited entry to over 40+ attractions at WDW. 

•It’s $15 per person, per day
•Guests can pay an additional price for Lightning Lane access to select attractions, up to 2 a day (think top tier rides like Tron, Seven Dwarves, etc)
•The times can be booked day of, guests will select the next available return time. Goodbye to the 60 day window!
•Onsite guests will get access to Lightning Lane at 7 am, offsite guests and APs will have to wait for the park to open 
.
. 
.
.
.
.

node.text:
❓What do you think of the new Disney Genie announcement? Let us know in the comments!
 
🧞‍♂️ Yesterday Disney dropped huge news with the announcement of Disney Genie, and we’re breaking it down for you! SAVE this post to refer back to!

Disney Genie is a new system that will be added to the My Disney Experience app. Here’s some of the things you can expect. 

🍂 This system will be introduced Fall 2021!

⚡️ Genie+ - A new $15 per person per day ($20 for Disneyland), system that replaces Fastpass+. The new line entrance called the Lightning Lane.

3️⃣ No more 3 Fastpass limit or 60 day booking in advance. If you pay for Genie+, day of, you can choose the next available time to ride an attraction. 

🎢 E-ticket rides - Guests can pay an additional added fee per ride (based on date, time, etc) for some of the big ticket attractions like Seven Dwarves Mine Train. 

👨‍👨‍👧‍👧 Recommendations built into the app. Based on your selections, Disney Genie will recommend rides, attractions, and more. 

⏰ Live wait times, letting you know the best time to ride and the forecasted wait. 

🍲 Mobile ordering will be available on Disney Genie, similar to My Disney Experience. 

Questions? Ask in the comments!
.
. 
.
.
.
.

node.text:
❓ In the comments, let us know your favorite place to stay at Disney because…

‼️ …WE’RE HERE! Details about our trip below!

🏠 THE HOTEL: We are so excited to be #hosted at the @courtyardlakebv! We have a king suite that connects to a room with two queens, so there’s plenty of space for the whole family, including living area to relax in at night. Stay tuned for a full post on this hotel coming soon 👀

🌳 DAY ONE, PART ONE: Today, we’ll be starting at Animal Kingdom! Our priorities at Animal Kingdom are Flight Of Passage, Everest, the Safari, maybe Dinosaur, and lunch at Satulii. If we have extra time, we’ll probably check out one of the exploration trails!

✨ DAY ONE, PART TWO: For the second half of the day, we’ll hop to Magic Kingdom and will try to hit as many rides as possible (probably based on the wait times). We have dinner reservations at Liberty Tree Tavern, and then are watching Happily Ever After (my favorite nighttime show of ALL TIME)!

🎥 DAY TWO, PART ONE: On Thursday, we’ll be starting at Hollywood Studios and are hoping to do Rise of the Resistence, Smuggler’s Run, Rockin Roller Coaster, Tower of Terror, Toy Story Mania, AND Runaway Railway, as well as lunch at Docking Bay Seven 😬

🌐 DAY TWO, PART TWO: Whenever we’re done at Hollywood, we’ll hop to Epcot to try as much as possible from Food & Wineb We may sneak in a ride at Soarin’ (TBD based on wait times) and will definitely end the night with Epcot Forever ❤️
.
.
.
.
.

node.text:
❓ What’s your favorite land in Magic Kingdom?

💡 The backstory of Tomorrowland is that it’s an intergalactic space port and functions as a full working city. One important part of this relates to the metallic palm trees that can be seen in the back of this photo.

🌴 They’re called Power Palms and were developed by the Tomorrowland Power Company. They were created to capture energy from the sun, which is then stored in coconut-shaped globes that hang from the trees. When the globes are full, the Power Company harvests them and uses the energy to power Tomorrowland!

👀 Keep your eyes out for one Power Palm in Tomorrowland that’s all folded up and doesn’t have any coconuts. This is because the power from that tree has already been harvested!
.
.
.
.
.

node.text:
❓ What’s your favorite dessert to eat on Disney property?

📸 DISNEY DESSERT FOOD REVIEW! The past few trips we’ve tried so many different desserts (these pictures don’t even cover them all). See below for some of our reviews and recommendations!

1️⃣ Num Num Cookie from Municiberg: A must-try and perfect for sharing. 10/10

2️⃣ Churros and chocolate dip from Pecos Bill: First time trying this but a classic Disney churro. 8.5/10

3️⃣ Vegan ice cream from Boardwalk Ice Cream: I love finding vegan options in the parks and this did not disappoint! 9/10 

4️⃣ Cheshire Cat Tail from Lunching Pad: Another one of our go-to’s, simple but delicious. 9.5/10

5️⃣ Local Wildflower Honey-Mascarpone Cheesecake from The Honey Bee-stro: Delicious, refreshing, and very light! 9/10

6️⃣ Fried Cinnamon Roll Bites from Sunshine Griddle: Doughy and an amazing breakfast treat. 9/10

7️⃣ Pecan Pie from Flower and Garden Festival: Really good sauce and whipped cream but a little dry. 8/10 

8️⃣Ooey Gooey Toffee Cake from Liberty Tree Tavern: Amazing in every way (except I’m very lactose intolerant hahah). 10/10

9️⃣ Lemon Cake with Strawberries from Hollywood and Vine: Sadly a bit disappointing, didn’t love any desserts here.  5/10 

🔟 Cinnamon Bun from Gaston’s Tavern: Perfect for sharing, be sure to ask for the extra free icing! 8/10
.
.
.
.
.

node.text:
❓How old were you when you first rode Tower of Terror? We never did it as kids and only tried it in our early teen years!
 
⚡️ This fact about the Tower of Terror might shock you. The screams you hear while waiting in line? Most of them are prerecorded!

🌀 While there are many screams that are real, Disney doesn’t pipe them into the queue. You never know what guests will say, and the screams Disney chose definitely set the mood for the ride!
.
. 
.
.
.
.

node.text:
❓Have you ever done a tour at Disney? Let us know which in the comments! 
 
🌐In 2019 we did the UnDISCOVERed Future World tour at Epcot. This tour took us through all the future world pavilions - we learned the history, cut the line to do the rides, and got to go in many of the private lounges! We also went backstage Epcot which was awesome. 

📷 One of the coolest things we got to do was hold a piece of a dinosaur animatronic from Ellen’s Universe of Energy, and see a bunch of behind the scenes photos! 

➡️Swipe to see pictures!!
.
. 
.
.
.
.

node.text:
❓Have you ever eaten at Woody’s Lunch Box in Toy Story Land? What’s your go-to order? 

🤠 Next time you walk through Toy Story Land, look for the giant cereal box of Lass-O’s. At the top, you’ll see Battle Creek listed. 

🥣 This is actually a tribute to Battle Creek, Michigan, where Kellogg’s cereal brand was founded! We absolutely love these clever details the Imagineers leave in the parks. 
.
. 
.
.
.
.
